# Component Reuse Before New Components

When new logic needs a component, first check whether an existing component already fits the use case or can be extended cleanly.

- Search the relevant package for existing components, hooks, and composition patterns before creating a new component.
- Prefer extending an existing component when the new behavior is compatible with its responsibility and API.
- Keep extensions small and cohesive; do not add broad boolean-prop combinations or unrelated behavior to force reuse.
- Create a new component when reuse would make the existing component harder to understand, less focused, or incompatible with current callers.
- Match the existing component style, naming, and import conventions in the package being edited.
